<TITLE> Hurricane closes in on coast: official </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Mongla, Nov 15 (bdnews24.com)  Strong winds came over Mongla, Heron Point and other places, witnesses said Thursday afternoon. The hurricane SIDR was 132 kilometres off Heron Point, Shah Alam, harbour master for the Mongla Port Authority, told bdnews24.com by phone. The hurricane may strike the Sundarbans in two hours, he said. The weather office said Khepupara and Dublar Char in the south also experienced heavy winds. Strong winds accompanied by driving rain started blowing through the Sundarbans and adjoining areas, bdnews24.com's correspondent Monir Hossain Kamal reported from the south. The vesselMV Abashar hired for BBC's river tour named "Bangladesh by river"got stuck, 25 kilometres off Sirajganj town, because of the bad weather, a journalist aboard the vessel told bdnews24.com by phone. bdne
